00:00:02.933 --> 00:00:08.499
Samsung Knox Suite is our all-in-one package of enterprise device management services

2
00:00:08.500 --> 00:00:11.766
bundled into three plans to best fit your business.

3
00:00:11.766 --> 00:00:15.999
The Knox Suite - Base Plan is our free device management plan that allows you to easily

4
00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
set up and secure your EMM and UEM managed devices.

5
00:00:20.300 --> 00:00:26.800
To get started with Samsung Knox Suite, you'll need to register for an account at samsungknox.com

6
00:00:26.800 --> 00:00:33.633
When you sign up, select the Knox Suite – Base Plan to use our free device management and enrollment services.

7
00:00:33.700 --> 00:00:37.700
To help you seamlessly prepare your devices for your business operations

8
00:00:37.700 --> 00:00:41.266
The Knox Suite – Base Plan includes Knox Mobile Enrollment

9
00:00:41.266 --> 00:00:44.099
our streamlined and secure device setup service

10
00:00:44.100 --> 00:00:49.266
which allows you to easily deploy your device fleet so they're ready for use right out of the box.

11
00:00:49.266 --> 00:00:50.599
To set this up,

12
00:00:50.600 --> 00:00:53.466
click Profiles under Knox Mobile Enrollment.

13
00:00:53.466 --> 00:00:58.999
Here, click Create profile and give your enrollment profile a name and description.

14
00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:01.600
At the bottom, select EMM.

15
00:01:01.600 --> 00:01:05.400
Optionally, you can also select Knox Service Plugin

16
00:01:05.400 --> 00:01:10.033
for additional device control and customization features at no additional cost.

17
00:01:10.733 --> 00:01:14.899
Click "Next" to configure your EMM and contact information.

18
00:01:14.900 --> 00:01:19.300
Then, select the EMM solution to enroll your devices to.

19
00:01:19.300 --> 00:01:22.600
Click Next to configure additional settings for enrollment

20
00:01:22.600 --> 00:01:28.133
which allows you to add additional enrollment methods, choose whether system apps are pre-installed

21
00:01:28.133 --> 00:01:31.799
configure enrollment screens and privacy policies, and more.

22
00:01:31.800 --> 00:01:36.133
Review your enrollment profile, then click Create and assign.

23
00:01:36.133 --> 00:01:39.733
Here, you can select which devices to assign to this profile.

24
00:01:39.733 --> 00:01:44.733
Assigned devices will automatically enroll to your EMM during initial device setup

25
00:01:44.733 --> 00:01:47.733
so they’re ready for business use right out of the box.

26
00:01:47.733 --> 00:01:55.233
To learn more about Knox Suite services and plans, please visit our documentation at docs.samsungknox.com

27
